<title>ITALY: No DPEF accord, no welfare reform talks - Italy union.</title>
<headline>No DPEF accord, no welfare reform talks - Italy union.</headline>
<dateline>ROME 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Sergio Cofferati, leader of Italy's biggest trades union, CGIL, said that without a prior accord between unions and majority on the contents of the government's economic target document (DPEF) the CGIL would not discuss any planned welfare state reforms.</p>
<p>&quot;Without an understanding on the DPEF, negotiatations on the welfare state won't get going. We want to know exactly the intentions of the government and the majority.</p>
<p>&quot;Too much gossip and chatter just creates allarmism,&quot; Cofferati told reporters attending the CISL trades union annual congress.</p>
<p>-- Rome newsroom +396 6782501</p>
